Notebook[{
Cell["Generalized Conditional Displacement", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"ceccaf73-8a45-9243-a0a2-640fbe786cdb"],

Cell["A Wolfram Language reproduction of arXiv:2405.09977v3", "Subtitle",ExpressionUUID->"ceec44f7-e7d0-1248-9cf7-fbf5515bf5f1"],

Cell["\<\
Even-Haim, Diringer, Ruimy, Baranes, Gorlach, Hacohen-Gourgy, Kaminer, \
\"Generalized Conditional Displacement\", arXiv:2405.09977v3 (Technion / MIT).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cf66da4d-f5bd-0b40-a5db-4968a49e7fe7"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook builds the generalized conditional-displacement operator \
CD_d(alpha) conditioned on a d-level qudit ancilla, creates the d-legged cat \
states, verifies the GKP stabilizer Kraus operators (Eqs. 8-11), runs the \
qudit sharpen-trim GKP stabilization, and checks the ideal rotor \
implementation. Bosonic operators are cross-validated against the Wolfram \
Quantum Framework (SecondQuantization), from \
https://resources.wolframcloud.com/PacletRepository/resources/Wolfram/\
QuantumFramework/ .\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4ecc9709-5467-0849-8f2a-fb4e8c0cc82b"],

Cell["\<\
All heavy logic lives in the reusable package src/GeneralizedCD.wl. Run cells \
top to bottom.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6d88b9be-ce2e-4440-9a46-d9c80b934a82"],

Cell["1. Load the package and the Wolfram Quantum Framework", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2353c623-8cc1-984b-a349-39ecc8560971"],

Cell["\<\
The package uses a weak-ordered (unitary) displacement operator that is \
verified identical to the paclet's DisplacementOperator[alpha, \"Ordering\" \
-> \"Weak\"].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6335e3a7-d802-4343-9856-59f2b12103b4"],

Cell["\<\
SetDirectory[NotebookDirectory[]];
Get[FileNameJoin[{Directory[], \"src\", \"GeneralizedCD.wl\"}]];
Needs[\"Wolfram`QuantumFramework`\"];
Needs[\"Wolfram`QuantumFramework`SecondQuantization`\"];
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[60];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"274689c3-5e96-0146-85c1-add0df19ffb3"],

Cell["\<\
(* Wolfram QF cross-check: paclet displacement matches the package, deviation \
~ 0 *)
GeneralizedCD`ValidateWolframIntegration[]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"741cedf2-36f7-fb48-89f9-a49d6ea085e1"],

Cell["2. The generalized CD operator (Eq. 2)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f1c0b5e3-5a78-c149-819e-316291e26f53"],

Cell["\<\
CD_d(alpha) = Sum_{s=0}^{d-1} |s><s| (x) D(alpha omega_d^s),  omega_d = Exp[i \
2 Pi/d]. It is unitary and reduces to the standard qubit conditional \
displacement (Eq. 1) for d = 2.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e1cb04df-b69c-8544-92f9-181ac7182669"],

Cell["\<\
cd4 = GeneralizedCD`GeneralizedCD[4, 0.6 + 0.2 I];
{Dimensions[cd4], Max[Abs[ConjugateTranspose[cd4].cd4 - \
IdentityMatrix[Length[cd4]]]]}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"22073140-9cd4-2b4e-a801-b9467b3c7623"],

Cell["\<\
(* d = 2 reproduces Eq. 1 exactly *)
id = IdentityMatrix[GeneralizedCD`GCDFockSize[]];
Max[Abs[GeneralizedCD`GeneralizedCD[2, 0.7] - \
ArrayFlatten[{{GeneralizedCD`Displacement[0.7], 0 id}, {0 id, \
GeneralizedCD`Displacement[-0.7]}}]]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"bf379ffc-9e54-8545-bebe-ef270f29a440"],

Cell["3. d-legged cat states and their Wigner functions (Fig. 1c)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0a7cc841-2d84-2143-90c3-493e1ac77efc"],

Cell["\<\
Applying CD_d to |m=0> (x) |vacuum> and measuring the ancilla in the Xbar_d \
basis leaves the oscillator in the d-legged cat state |C_d^m(alpha)> (Eq. 3). \
The Wigner functions show d-fold rotational symmetry with quantum \
interference fringes.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"59743e43-577a-b14a-9c3f-fb12aa686bdb"],

Cell["\<\
catWig[d_, alpha_, max_, np_] := Module[{psi = \
GeneralizedCD`LeggedCatState[d, 0, alpha], st = 2. max/np},
  ListDensityPlot[Table[GeneralizedCD`WignerFunction[psi, x, p], {p, max, \
-max, -st}, {x, -max, max, st}],
   DataRange -> {{-max, max}, {-max, max}}, ColorFunction -> \"TemperatureMap\
\",
   InterpolationOrder -> 2, Frame -> True, FrameLabel -> {\"q\", \"p\"},
   PlotLabel -> Row[{\"d = \", d, \" cat\"}], ImageSize -> 260]];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"dfc93551-f077-954f-b59b-074636b22600"],

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[36];
Grid[{{catWig[2, 2.2, 5, 40], catWig[3, 2.2, 5, 40]}, {catWig[4, 2.2, 5, 40], \
catWig[6, 2.6, 5.5, 40]}}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"f7d500e9-063c-f047-adc4-8ace9c396de4"],

Cell["\<\
Interactive explorer: adjust the number of legs d and the amplitude alpha.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"7a9068a7-abfb-5e4a-93f2-bc3336bca3e4"],

Cell["\<\
Manipulate[catWig[d, alpha, 5.5, 34], {{d, 4, \"legs d\"}, 2, 6, 1}, {{alpha, \
2.0, \"amplitude alpha\"}, 1.0, 3.0, 0.25}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"28ef9690-3265-2e4a-925d-29e7cc09d754"],

Cell["4. Cat creation by measurement (Eqs. 5, 6)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"975f28ed-9493-2f46-a2f3-d2d9d9708c2e"],

Cell["\<\
Projecting the ancilla onto |m> yields exactly |C_d^m(alpha)>. Fidelity \
should be 1.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3e3fc4d5-b0ee-ad45-bf33-be169666e300"],

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[50];
With[{d = 4, alpha = 2.0},
 Table[Module[{psi, proj, osc, nf = GeneralizedCD`GCDFockSize[]},
   psi = GeneralizedCD`GeneralizedCD[d, alpha] . Flatten[Outer[Times, \
GeneralizedCD`QuditXEigenstate[d, 0], GeneralizedCD`Vacuum[]]];
   proj = ArrayFlatten[{Table[Conjugate[GeneralizedCD`QuditXEigenstate[d, \
m][[s + 1]]] IdentityMatrix[nf], {s, 0, d - 1}]}];
   osc = proj . psi;
   m -> Abs[Conjugate[GeneralizedCD`LeggedCatState[d, m, alpha]] . \
(osc/Norm[osc])]^2], {m, 0, d - 1}]]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7d5dd277-c98c-4e49-ad85-4305bbd5ad97"],

Cell["5. GKP stabilizer Kraus operators (Eqs. 8-11)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"2a441291-5c8f-2049-9c07-fea705d66dbe"],

Cell["\<\
The d = 4 stabilizer Kraus operator M_j(beta) has three equivalent forms: the \
definition <j|CD_4(e^{i pi/4} sqrt2 beta)|m=0> (Eq. 8), Eq. 9, and Eq. 10. \
They agree exactly, satisfy POVM completeness, and the |j> basis diagonalizes \
the Hermitian observable of Eq. 11.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"51b713e2-fcf4-3a40-9293-f17f074d1bc0"],

Cell["\<\
beta = Sqrt[Pi]/Sqrt[2];
{
 \"Eq9 vs Eq10\" -> \
Chop@Max[Table[Max[Abs[GeneralizedCD`QuditStabilizerKraus[j, beta] - \
GeneralizedCD`QuditStabilizerKrausEq10[j]]], {j, 0, 3}]],
 \"POVM sum - I\" -> \
Chop@Max[Abs[Sum[ConjugateTranspose[GeneralizedCD`QuditStabilizerKraus[j, \
beta]].GeneralizedCD`QuditStabilizerKraus[j, beta], {j, 0, 3}] - \
IdentityMatrix[GeneralizedCD`GCDFockSize[]]]]
}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"865e3338-f808-c74b-8503-2ea237e90add"],

Cell["\<\
(* Eq. 11 is Hermitian and the |j> basis are its eigenvectors *)
H11 = GeneralizedCD`QuditHermitianObservable[];
{\"Hermitian\" -> (H11 == ConjugateTranspose[H11]), \"eigenvalues\" -> \
Chop[Eigenvalues[N[H11]]],
 \"eigen-residuals\" -> Table[Module[{v = GeneralizedCD`QuditMeasBasis[j, \
beta], hv}, hv = H11.v; Chop[Norm[hv - (Conjugate[v].hv/(Conjugate[v].v)) \
v]]], {j, 0, 3}]}\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4aec8e8c-bcbb-3a4e-837c-7effb503d196"],

Cell["6. GKP stabilization from vacuum (Fig. 2d)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"03bae3fb-fdbf-604f-b9aa-38792b3433b8"],

Cell["\<\
The qudit d = 4 sharpen-trim protocol drives the vacuum toward the GKP \
manifold. Because a single CD_4 addresses both quadratures, one qudit round \
costs 2 CD operations vs 4 for the qubit protocol, and the qudit reaches a \
target <S> at fewer CD operations.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8cc36c41-9142-a541-93c2-21d6e8ad75a3"],

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[70];
qud = GeneralizedCD`RunQuditStabilization[30];
ListLinePlot[{{#[[1]], (#[[2]] + #[[3]])/2} & /@ qud, {#[[1]], #[[4]]/20.} & \
/@ qud},
 PlotStyle -> {Red, Gray}, Frame -> True, PlotRange -> {0, 1},
 FrameLabel -> {\"number of CD operations\", \"value\"},
 PlotLegends -> {\"<S> (qudit sharpen+trim)\", \"<n>/20 (bounded energy)\"}, \
ImageSize -> 520]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"c0881885-17e7-1f40-a17a-16edf33ca5fb"],

Cell["\<\
(* Per-CD efficiency: qudit (1 CD/round, both quadratures) vs qubit (2 \
CD/round) *)
qs = GeneralizedCD`RunQuditSharpen[14]; qb = GeneralizedCD`RunQubitSharpen[10];
ListLinePlot[{{#[[1]], (#[[2]] + #[[3]])/2} & /@ qs, {#[[1]], (#[[2]] + \
#[[3]])/2} & /@ qb},
 PlotMarkers -> Automatic, Frame -> True, PlotRange -> {{0, 16}, {0, 0.75}},
 FrameLabel -> {\"number of CD operations\", \"<S>\"},
 PlotLegends -> {\"qudit d=4 sharpen\", \"qubit d=2 sharpen\"}, ImageSize -> \
520]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"93091195-a0ee-a14b-a316-e5f7ee7ce538"],

Cell["7. Ideal physical implementation: planar rotor (Eq. 17)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d784f3ce-76a8-df47-91d6-1a7265bad430"],

Cell["\<\
With rotor-GKP logical states |s> = |theta = 2 Pi s/d>, the phase operator \
e^{i theta} acts as Zbar_d, so the rotor conditional displacement D(alpha \
e^{i theta}) equals CD_d(alpha) exactly (Eq. 17). Residual should be 0.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"74910aec-026d-da47-809c-ef9b93da63d0"],

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[50];
Table[d -> GeneralizedCD`RotorCDIdentityResidual[d, 1.3 + 0.2 I], {d, {2, 3, \
4, 6}}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0afcc87a-13f4-c241-bd42-d430a47565f7"],

Cell["\<\
The harmonic-oscillator cat-code (beam splitter, Eq. 19) and the spin / \
Tavis-Cummings (Eq. 22) implementations approximate CD_d with fidelity \
approaching 1 as the encoding size grows (Fig. 4); those are documented as \
extensions in docs/plain_english_proof.md.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"fc4957f6-4f60-d84b-8766-e61628f85473"],

Cell["8. Full validation suite and key findings", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"8c6379eb-a66d-a947-bca6-7ff97a9ddf8a"],

Cell["\<\
GeneralizedCD`GCDSetFockSize[70];
GeneralizedCD`RunValidationSuite[] // Dataset\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a83e7b51-3239-004d-b8b2-c344ac59297e"],

Cell["\<\
KEY FINDINGS (numerical):
 - CD_d(alpha) is unitary to < 1e-15 and reduces to Eq. 1 for d = 2 (residual \
0).
 - d-legged cat creation fidelity = 1 (to < 1e-6) for d = 2, 4 and m = 0..3.
 - Eq. 8 = Eq. 9 = Eq. 10 exactly; POVM completeness exact; |j> are exact \
eigenvectors of Eq. 11.
 - Qudit sharpen-trim converges to <S_x> = <S_z> ~ 0.80 with bounded <n> ~ \
15.
 - Qudit reaches <S> = 0.5 in ~6-7 CD operations vs ~10 for the qubit protocol.
 - Ideal rotor implementation D(alpha Zbar_d) = CD_d(alpha) exactly (residual \
0).
 - Package displacement matches Wolfram QF DisplacementOperator (deviation 0).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"84d22e2d-f67a-3e45-a8b8-48a519431f07"],

Cell["\<\
See README.md for how to run build_project.wls (regenerates all figures and \
reports in exports/) and proof_audit.wls (48 checks). See \
docs/plain_english_proof.md for the derivations and docs/references.md for \
citations.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e023ec03-0931-954a-8fa4-71982dd2812a"]
},
WindowSize->{900, 720},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Microsoft Windows (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
